It’s not strange for a woman to love jewelry. But perhaps, I am the strange one because I have loved them since I was a young girl. You might think the shine and the glitter were the reasons. You’re wrong.
I love jewelry because I see them as a medium to represent yourself. It’s a small piece that sends a silent expression. Each piece contributes uniquely to style and appearances.
The most attractive element of jewelry, in my view, is its inherent history, whether it be a personal memory or the thought of the gift-giver. Every little bracelet or pair of earrings carries its own personal value beyond the monetary one, since it is attached to some memory.
Jewelry can also completely transform an outfit in terms of its aesthetics. Whenever I wear something modest, I know for sure that with the right jewelry, the result will be much better.
The choice is very vast, and there is such an array of different items that you may easily pick up whatever suits you best depending on your mood or occasion. For instance, today you may fancy an elegant or chick look. Perhaps, tomorrow you want to wear striking or eye-catching pieces. 

People may see jewelry as a decoration. But I see things differently. For me, it is a piece for celebrating your individuality. In this day and age, that’s what matters the most.

